Below are targeted diffs to reduce branching overhead in the hot numba‐compiled routines and to ensure the very first multi‐start uses the true equispaced configuration (which for s=1 in 1D is already the global minimizer). Removing those tiny “if dx<1e-12” checks in the inner loops will both simplify the code and reduce mispredicted branches, and switching seed 0 to an equispaced start gives you the exact optimum immediately for n=20, s=1.

